Dangote Cement Plans $3.9 Billion Expansion, BusinessDay Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-04-13T08:15:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/dangote-cement-plans-3-9-billion-expansion-businessday-says.html
Dangote Cement Plc (DANGCEM)  plans to spend
$3.9 billion boosting its capacity in  Africa  by 16.5 million
tons by 2013,  BusinessDay said , citing Chairman  Aliko Dangote .  Dangote aims to increase cement production on the continent
to 50 million tons a year, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Agnes Nikoi at   anikoi@bloomberg.net  